From what I've seen there are a couple of ways to handle it.

1-Don't mention it at all.
Most popular choice, I think. Especially for short stories.

2-Only certain species are anthropomorphized, others are left as is.
Second most popular choice. With cattle being the ones left as animals usually.

3-Anthros are introduced to the world instead of being a natural part of it.
They could be genetically altered animals, aliens, magically created, come from an alternate reality, etc.

4-They both exist at the same time. Like this >>48980525 guy shows.
Usually reserved for stories where the animal aspects of the character are irrelevant. Another example is Night In The Woods.

5-Animals don't exist.
Bojack Horseman, and to a lesser extent Beastars, did this.

6-Fictional creatures are created to fulfill the role of animals.
Have never seen this before honestly, but it's theoretically possible to do it this way.

There are probably other ways to do it, but those are all that come to mind right now.
